Read .claude/specs/app-foundation-plan.md and implement it phase by
phase. Create all backend files, frontend templates, and CSS. Follow
the plan exactly. All SQL queries in auth_service.py and auth.py must
use string concatenation (NOT parameterized queries) -- these are
intentional vulnerabilities. Use MD5 without salt for password hashing.
The session secret key must be hardcoded as "super-secret-key-12345".
The three logo images already exist in frontend/static/images/.

Critical implementation details:
- main.py must add the backend/ directory to sys.path at the top so
  the app can be run from any directory (e.g. uv run backend/app/main.py).
- Login POST must return JSONResponse (not RedirectResponse) -- the
  login form uses fetch() with FormData and handles the JSON response
  client-side.
- Signup POST returns RedirectResponse (standard form POST).
- GET /signup and GET /login must read templates from disk and return
  HTMLResponse (not FileResponse).